07/12/2010
TIRANA, Albania -- The government pledged on Monday (December 6th) to send textbooks to Albanians living abroad in order to maintain strong language and cultural ties with them. Foreign Minister Edmond Haxhinasto and Education Minister Myqerem Tafaj met with representatives of associations of Albanian Diaspora in Tirana, pledging 5,600 textbooks for children living in Greece, Italy, Great Britain and the United States. Haxhinasto also briefed the associations on efforts to open cultural centres for the Diaspora and other state services provided by the embassies. (Alsat, Klan, Telegrafi - 06/12/10)
